340 g Pork Chops, boneless
1 unit(s) Yellow Onion
7.5 g Chicken Stock Powder
4 g Garlic Salt
170 g Fusilli
227 g Broccoli
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
10 g Cream Sauce Spice Blend
1 tbsp Oil*
2 tbsp Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 425°F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over high.
To the boiling water, add fusilli. Cook for 5 min.
After fusilli has cooked for 5 min, add broccoli to pot with fusilli. Cook for 3-5 min, stirring occasionally, unitl pasta is tender and broccoli is tender-crisp.
Strain fusilli and broccoli, then return to the pot, off heat.

Meanwhile, p eel, then cut onion into 1/2-inch pieces.
Pat the pork dry with paper towels. Season with 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) garlic salt and pepper.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium. When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil and pork. Pan-fry pork for 1-2 min per side, until golden.
Transfer pork to a baking sheet. Roast in the middle of the oven for 8-10 min, until pork is cooked through.**

Meanwhile, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter to the same pan, then swirl the pan to melt. Add onions to the same pan. Cook for 2-3 min, scraping any brown bits from the pan until onions soften.
Sprinkle over the Cream Sauce Spice Blend. Cook for 30 sec, stirring often, until onions are coated.

Whisk in the stock powder and 3/4 cup (1 1/2 cup) water. Cook for 1-2 min, stirring often, until sauce simmers and thickens slightly.
Remove the pan from heat.
Whisk in sour cream.

To the noodles in pot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter. Stir to coat.
Season with 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) garlic salt and pepper, then toss to combine.

Thinly slice the pork.
Stir in any remaining juices from the baking sheet into the sauce.
Divide the noodles and broccoli between plates.
Top with pork, then sauce.